    "desc": "Ranked among the nation’s best colleges, Carleton College is a small, private liberal arts college in the historic river town of Northfield, Minnesota.",
    "navbar": "",
    "text": "COVID-19 Response Make a Gift\nAdmissionsAcademicsAthleticsAbout Carleton\nfor Alumni\nStudents\nFaculty/Staff\nFamilies\nOffices/DepartmentsDirectoryMapPhotosNewsEventsMore\nWhat sets Carleton apart?\nUnmatched teaching in a close-knit community where intellectual curiosity leads to a lifetime of exploration.\nLearn From the Best\nOur faculty are as enthusiastic about learning as you are.\n#1\nin teaching\nyear after year\n8:1\nstudent-faculty ratio\nOn the Right Track\nSix newly tenured faculty are studying machine learning, Bronze Age Greece, Chinese microblogging, and much more.\nOur Standout Faculty\nFind Your Place\nThe Carleton community is known for being warm, welcoming, and willing to debate and discuss anything.\nCampus Tour\nExplore the Carleton Community\nImagine it. Do it.\nCarleton’s liberal arts focus gives you the freedom to explore deeply and broadly, in and out of the classroom.\n54\nmajors & minors\nJust a few of our 1,000 courses:\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTheater 238\nCostume Design for Theater\nMathematics 333\nCombinatorial Theory\nBiology 368\nDevelopmental Neurobiology\n222\nstudent-created, student-led organizations\n72%\nof Carls play varsity, club, or intramural sports\nOutside the Classroom Majors & Minors\nPowerful Post-Grad Support\nCarleton and its alumni community work together as a network to launch you on your chosen path.\nANY MAJOR. ANY CAREER.\nHow Carls apply their majors to life\n95%\nof grads are employed full-time or attending graduate or professional school six months after graduation\n$464k\nsupport for internships last summer\nAfter Carleton\nOur Commitment to Affordability\n0\n%\nWe meet 100% of your family’s eligibility for need-based financial aid.\n$\n0\n.\n0\nM\nWe distribute $62.7M in financial aid to Carleton students annually.\n$\n0\n,\n0\nOur average 2021 need-based financial aid award was $57,000.\nOne North College St\nNorthfield, MN 55057\nUSA\n507-222-4000\nAdmissions\nAcademics\nAthletics\nAbout Carleton\nEmployment\nGiving\nDirectory\nMap\nPhotos\nEvents\nNews\nfor Alumni\nStudents\nFaculty/Staff\nFamilies\nPrivacyAccessibilityTerms of Use\nCarleton College is an equal opportunity educator and employer.",
